The paper deals with automatic melody generation using machine learning techniques, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the representation of musical properties as unique 'words,' which can be seen as a natural language processing (NLP) approach, falling under the sub-category of structured data (cs.SD). The regularization policies and conditioning on song part information can be seen as techniques for improving the quality of the generated output, which can be categorized under statistical learning (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
